sec.p:
As shown in Table 4, due to the contact of the gases with the hot TCR® char in the post-reformer, the reaction between carbon dioxide and the carbon in the hot char is stimulated, which leads to a formation of carbon monoxides. By the water–gas shifting reaction, the CO and water vapor can be further transformed into CO2 and H2. Furthermore, the higher reforming temperature increases the de-carbonization and decarboxylation of the oxygenated compounds in the products, which leads to the production of more CO and CO2.Table 4
